So if you’ve been following me for a while you’ve probably seen me use tracing paper for try-see’s I realize how much better clear film is for this purpose! I work in such a meticulous way, I go into detail before I’ve made final decisions, the way I work is very organic and the work unfolds itself as I go and I evolve my ideas as I see color shape and co tent take form …this is a part of my process …over the years I’ve thought it was a wrong way or cumbersome way to work and attempted to change my process which has NEVER worked for me so eventually I had to accept that my process it’s just the way things work for me.  I’ve been making art for a long ass time so it’s silly to self-judge my methods at this point. For the youngsters Part of finding your own unique voice is not thinking that you have to create in a certain way for it to be “right” but find what is right for you. Sorry for the mini rant , I’m in the early stages of a new body of work for 2024 and so there’s lots of studies happening right now… and as it turns out even my studies, such as this, get way involved, if they had feelings they’d probably be mad in the end that I call them studies 😂 but I digress.. back to the try-see.. if nothing else I learned that I love that English red color here and it’s gonna have to be in there if not hair then something else!! #jennybird #jennybirdart #oilpaintingstudy #oilpaint #surrealportrait #fineartist #artistprocess #artistmethods #neosurrealism

Flashing back 18 years ago to this small painting on paper titled Lovebite. This motif as been a running theme in my work most of my adult life. I was looking for something to post from 2006 because that was the first year I started seeing my therapist. I don’t often post personal things on here but for 18 years I had her to talk to and she was with me for the lion share of my professional career and talking to her about the ups and downs and inside outs of being a human and an artist was something that was hard at times but I cherished and she helped me so much. My therapist died unexpectedly in Feb. and it’s been pretty hard not having her here , I hold all the conversations in my heart and mind and can think about what she might say to me about this or that feeling that comes up .
, but still , knowing I can’t call her up to talk to her again really sucks. She was with me through a huge evolution of not only my self but my artwork and I miss her and will continue to miss having her with me on my path.  _______________________.  The second pic is from her early career when she was a young actress. Wasn’t she adorable?💗

Not posting much, social media sometimes gets me down, it’s distracting to my process as an artist. I’ve spent so much of my life solitary in my practice with people only seeing work when a show is completed. I hate feeling that I’m supposed to be a performing monkey (no offense to monkeys) online. I feel so torn now about whether to keep things private or post what I’m working on so I’m doing a halfway post here, this is me playing around with a painting that’s already been shown , I’m always interested in patterns so I’m creating some of my own, I need to rework this and not have the devil girl repeat so close together but it’s fun and a first go, I ordered a little wallpaper sample of this just for fun. #fineartist #surrealistwallpaper #devilgirl #canyouhearme #botanicalart #jennybirdalcantara #jennybird

I don’t do New Year’s resolutions but I do think we tend to like markers of time and the idea that we use a fresh, clean spanking new day like the first day of a New Year, even though every day is a fresh spanking new day, it maybe gives us a little feeling of an opportunity that we don’t always afford ourselves, to start anew , and that’s not a bad thing, so that’s a long winded way to say I’m gonna try this year to post more in process videos this year even if they are just studies like this one. Of course it is the second and not the first of the year so if I fail it’s not as bad right? 😂 #oilstudy #jennybird #workinprocess #sleepybunny
